# React Component Rules

## Structure Rules
- ALWAYS use named exports — never default export from component files
- ALWAYS define Props interface ABOVE the component function
- ALWAYS destructure props in the function signature
- NEVER use `React.FC` type — use plain function declaration
- ONE component per file — no exceptions

## Props Patterns
- ALWAYS type `children` as `React.ReactNode`
- ALWAYS include `className?: string` for composable components
- USE optional props with sensible defaults
- NEVER pass raw setState functions as props — use callbacks

## Styling
- ALWAYS use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- ALWAYS use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for conditional classes
- NEVER use inline styles except for truly dynamic values
- ALWAYS use shadcn/ui as base components, extend with Tailwind
- USE `cva()` for components with multiple variants

## Component Categories
- `components/ui/` — base shadcn/ui components only
- `components/shared/` — reusable business components
- `components/[feature]/` — feature-specific components
- `app/` — page-level components (server components)

## Example — Correct Pattern
```typescript
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'

interface FeatureCardProps {
  title: string
  description: string
  icon: React.ReactNode
  onClick?: () => void
  isLoading?: boolean
  className?: string
}

export function FeatureCard({
  title,
  description,
  icon,
  onClick,
  isLoading = false,
  className,
}: FeatureCardProps) {
  return (
    

      
{icon}

      
{title}

      

{description}


      {onClick && (
        
          {isLoading ? 'Loading...' : 'Get Started'}
        
      )}
    

  )
}
```
